  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the recruitment process of Accenture?",
  "response": "The recruitment process at Accenture typically involves several stages. While specific details can vary depending on the role, location, and business needs, the general framework often includes the following steps:\n\n1. **Application Submission:**\n   - Interested candidates submit their resume and application through the Accenture careers website or via job portals.\n\n2. **Initial Screening:**\n   - The HR team reviews applications to shortlist candidates who meet the basic requirements of the role.\n\n3. **Assessment Tests:**\n   - Candidates may be required to take online assessments, which can include aptitude tests, technical skills evaluations, or psychometric testing.\n\n4. **HR Interview:**\n   - A preliminary interview with HR focuses on the candidate's background, experience, and fit for Accenture's culture.\n\n5. **Technical Interview(s):**\n   - For technical roles, candidates undergo interviews with subject matter experts to assess their technical competencies and problem-solving skills.\n\n6. **Managerial Interview:**\n   - In some cases, candidates meet with potential managers to discuss their experience, expectations, and how they align with the team's needs.\n\n7. **Case Study/Simulation:**\n   - Certain roles may require candidates to complete a case study or simulation exercise to demonstrate their abilities in real-world scenarios.\n\n8. **Final Interview:**\n   - A final interview can take place to evaluate the overall fit and address any remaining questions from both sides.\n\n9. **Offer and Onboarding:**\n   - Successful candidates receive an offer letter detailing the terms of employment. Upon acceptance, the onboarding process begins, including orientation and integration into Accenture.\n\nThroughout the process, Accenture values a thorough evaluation of both technical capabilities and cultural fit, aiming to select candidates who not only possess the required skills but also align with their corporate values and work environment.",
